Climate change at each site

These figures show how the climate change has changed at each site. Blue points represent historical climate and red represent modern climate. Temperature has increased and precipitation has decreased at each site.

Are mammals tracking climate?

These plots compare changes in the community temperature index and community precipitation index with observed climate change at each site. Most sites are not keeping up with climate change (red line).
